<div class="dnd_post-card__lower-section">
<h2 class="dnd_post-card_title">
<a href="https://granta.com/once-again-germany-defines-who-is-a-jew-part-ii/">
Once Again, Germany Defines Who Is a Jew | Part II
</a>
</h2>
<h4 class="dnd_post-card_author">
<a class="contributor-link" href="https://granta.com/contributor/george-prochnik/">George Prochnik</a>, <a class="contributor-link" href="https://granta.com/contributor/emily-dische-becker/">Emily Dische-Becker</a> & <a class="contributor-link" href="https://granta.com/contributor/eyal-weizman/">Eyal Weizman</a>
</h4>
<p class="dnd_post-card_text">
‘Turning to Germany, it seems that Jews are the only ones entitled to historical context, to history, and also to trauma. Palestinian history is denied.’ <br/><br/> George Prochnik in conversation with Emily Dische-Becker and Eyal Weizman, after 7 October 2023.
</p>
</div>
